			<td colspan="6" class="DetailTitle" style="text-align:center;">
                            Summary on Grant Application Form</td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td colspan="6" class="DetailValue" style="padding:5px;">
                        <span id="lblAbstract">The aim of this proposal is to study existence and stability of coherent localized structure in nonlinear wave equations and to understand the links between methods of partial differential equations (PDEs) and those of dynamical systems theory. Specifically, we focus on global time behavior of the modified NLS equation and the massive Thirring model (MTM), as well as their perturbations and generalizations. We employ the fad that these soliton equations are, in some special cases, completely integrable Hamiltonian systems n infinite dimensions, solvable by means of spectral theory of linear differential operators (ZakharovShabat operators and generalizations). The integrable PDE examples illustrate rich and fascinating global behavior of the localised structures. However, they do not indicate the generality of the phenomena. Once integrability is broken by a perturbation (dissipative or Hamiltonian) of the equation, properties of localised solutions are unknown. We analyze stability and persistence of localized solutions in unbounded and periodic bounded spatial domain, with important physical applications in photonic crystals, nonlinear optics, and fluid mechanics.</span>
                        </td>
		</tr>
